Step 1: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.
• From the balance sheet, the total liabilities are given by the "Total Current Liabilities", which is 1,124,588.25.
• The Total Assets are 15,288,131.32.
• Therefore, Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 1,124,588.25 / 15,288,131.32 ≈ 0.0735 (approximately 0.07 when rounded).

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio.
• From the cash flow statement, the Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities is 215,423.24.
• From the income statement, the Net Profit is 1,163,543.07.
• Therefore, Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = 215,423.24 / 1,163,543.07 ≈ 0.1852 (approximately 0.19 when rounded).

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.07",
    "Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio": "0.19"
  }
}
